        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName><sic>Pittsburg</sic></placeName> <date>December 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1852</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dear sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">by our last meeting of our<lb/> Congregation it has been resolved to advertise in<lb/> your Occident for a shochet teacher &#38; chasan<lb/> you will please then and <add>&#63;</add> the following adverti<lb/>sement in your Occident for three times and send<lb/> me by letter your charge for the same <sic>wich</sic> you shall<lb/> receive by return mail</p>
			<p>Wanted by the German Jewish Congregation Sharay Shomajim<add>&#63;</add><lb/> of <placeName><sic>Pittsburg</sic> Pa.</placeName> a Competent person to officiate as<lb/> chasan shochet &#38; teacher salary 250 Dollars per annum<lb/> he must bring satisfactory testimonial and the term<lb/> to <sic>comence</sic> on first of <date>April</date> next for <sic>farther</sic><lb/> information <sic>aply</sic> by letter Post paid.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">N. Gallinger</persName> here<lb/> our most <add>&#63;</add> is to get a Good teacher for our<lb/> <sic>youts</sic> as they are till now <sic>verry</sic> ignorant of our<lb/> <sic>relition</sic></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I am sir Respectfully yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">N. Gallinger</persName></p>
			<p>N. D. Abr. <persName>Leeser</persName> I want to <sic>inquir</sic> of you in the same time<lb/> about <persName>Mr E. Marcusson</persName> that Gentleman is here chasan<lb/> &#38; shochet by Polish Kahl and it has been hindet to<lb/> our Rahl that the Polish Kahl <sic>wand</sic> to unite</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>with our Rahl&#44; <sic>wich</sic> I believe would be a Good thing<lb/> for better and I <sic>understoot</sic> that they want our Kohl to<lb/> engage <persName>Mr Marcuson</persName> as their chasan&#44; it has nothing more<lb/> been said about it and I for my part are not<lb/> <sic>aquainted</sic> with <persName>Abr <add>&#63;</add></persName> no more than <add>&#63;</add><lb/> I did so in your <sic>Occitend</sic> but understood that he<lb/> could not teach the children the <sic>pronosation</sic> of<lb/> the German <del>teacher</del> reading <sic>wich</sic> would be an objective<lb/> Now sir I wish you would be so kind when you<lb/> let me know the amount of the advertisement to<lb/> give <sic>privatly</sic> your <sic>oppinion</sic> as I think you are<lb/> well <sic>aquainted</sic> with <persName>Mr Marcuson</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">I remain yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">N Galinger</persName></p>
          
        </body>
